<item>
            <title>[JCR-181] jcr-server should honor a webdav request&apos;s Content-Type and Content-Language headers</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-181</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>when processing a PUT or a POST, the DavResource should have access to the Content-Type and Content-Language headers presented in the webdav request, if any.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
when the client explicitly communicates these headers, their values should take priority over server calculations (such as that done in SetContentTypeCommand), or at least be input into server calculations&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
furthermore, the dav getcontentlanguage is not at all supported by at least the simple webdav server.&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
