                    <comment id="12319385" author="anchela" created="Sat, 20 Aug 2005 00:22:55 +0100"  >------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;br/&gt;
1) Content-Language&lt;br/&gt;
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;br/&gt;
- header value is set if present (retrieved from the dav resource)&lt;br/&gt;
- simple DavResourceImpl inits the content-langage dav property if it &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;is available from the resouce.&lt;br/&gt;
- extended export/importcontext so they honour content-language  prop.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;br/&gt;
2) ContentType/ContentLanguage when adding member resources&lt;br/&gt;
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;br/&gt;
modified the davresource in order to allow to pass a context rather than only an input stream to the addMember method. the context current provides contentype/contentlanguage/inputstream.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
regards&lt;br/&gt;
angela</comment>
